Nigerian Police Charged With Boko Haram Murders, Trust Newspaper Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-22T08:19:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/nigerian-police-charged-with-boko-haram-murders-trust-newspaper-says.html
Nigeria  charged two police
commissioners and a number of other officers with the murder of
three Boko Haram leaders arrested after a 2009 uprising by the
Islamic sect,  Daily Trust  said, citing an unidentified security
official.  Seventeen policemen were arrested after a video clip
emerged that showed the three leaders were executed after
capture, the Abuja-based newspaper said. The officers are
standing trial at a Federal High Court in Abuja.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 